Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.56,0:01:35.90,JoJo-EpTitle,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(614,472)}Episodio 21 {\fs17}The Mystery of Emperor Crimson
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.80,0:01:33.40,JoJo-main,Mista,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Damn it, Narancia!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.40,0:01:36.77,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Who do you think you are, \Ntrying to eat all the chocolates yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.77,0:01:38.01,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,Give them back!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.01,0:01:41.40,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,I bought them with my own \Nmoney, so give them back!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.20,0:01:42.41,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Narancia, I swear...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.40,0:01:43.76,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,There are only three left!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.78,0:01:44.41,JoJo-main,Abba,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}What a greedy little shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.76,0:01:46.12,JoJo-main,Mista,0000,0000,0000,,We've all been waiting for these, \Nand we're hungry!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.91,0:01:50.15,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,The ladybug brooch is moving \Nfrom the top of the tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.15,0:01:50.96,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,I can feel it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.44,0:01:53.13,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's heading to the charnel house below
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.13,0:01:54.76,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,to try to cross through there.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.16,0:01:58.68,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,Bucciarati must've put the brooch \Nsomewhere on the boss's clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.99,0:02:02.76,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Giorno, but could \Nyou grab that water?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.15,0:02:04.32,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a bit thirsty.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.90,0:02:07.77,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,Also, you should be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.77,0:02:12.11,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,We've been ordered to wait \Nhere on the boat for now,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.11,0:02:14.25,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,and not set foot on the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.25,0:02:15.00,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.99,0:02:20.69,JoJo-main,Mista,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.69,0:02:23.42,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You ate them, didn't you, Mista?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.42,0:02:26.75,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,Give them back, damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.75,0:02:29.04,JoJo-main,Mista,0000,0000,0000,,And what the hell do you have on your mouth?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.04,0:02:29.65,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.24,0:02:30.96,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.25,0:02:33.60,JoJo-main,Mista,0000,0000,0000,,"Ah," my ass! You little shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.60,0:02:35.55,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}S-So sweet!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.60,0:02:36.53,JoJo-main,Mista,0000,0000,0000,,When did you stuff them in your mouth?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.07,0:02:41.30,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, I didn't thank \Nyou yet, did I, Giorno?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.71,0:02:44.22,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,For grabbing the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.56,0:02:55.78,JoJo-internal/narrator,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,Something's... bizarre...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.73,0:03:06.41,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.52,0:03:09.01,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,but something's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.20,0:03:11.49,JoJo-main,Abba,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.49,0:03:14.79,JoJo-main,Abba,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you hear that the boss ordered \Nus not to set foot on the is—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.81,0:03:16.49,JoJo-main,Abba,0000,0000,0000,,...land?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.84,0:03:17.49,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.91,0:03:20.36,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.92,0:03:23.51,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,Something weird is going on!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.69,0:03:25.40,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't good! Bucciarati!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.40,0:03:27.44,JoJo-main,Abba,0000,0000,0000,,Where do you think you're going, Giorno?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.96,0:03:28.86,JoJo-internal/narrator,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Is that you, Giorno?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.86,0:03:29.81,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,Bucciarati!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.35,0:03:33.19,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I know he's on the move.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.19,0:03:36.77,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,I know exactly where the boss is because \Nof the brooch you put on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.77,0:03:39.82,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, he's at the bottom of \Nthe stairs to the charnel house.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.82,0:03:42.32,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,He's right by the pillar that's about \Ntwo meters away from the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.48,0:03:45.24,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,But wait, Bucciarati!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.24,0:03:47.91,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,Something is wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.65,0:03:54.17,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,Bucciarati, your mission to \Nact as Trish's bodyguard
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.61,0:03:56.92,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,has now come to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.89,0:04:07.35,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Why, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.61,0:04:10.10,JoJo-internal/narrator,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,He's trying to immobilize my arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.10,0:04:12.10,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Zipper Man!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.10,0:04:16.05,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,But... Emperor Crimson has already...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.50,0:04:31.58,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,...seen through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.29,0:04:34.30,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,Your movements in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.30,0:04:36.63,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,The trajectory of your \Nmovements in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.19,0:04:42.05,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,Within Emperor Crimson's ability, \Nthis world's time disappears,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.05,0:04:47.63,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,and no one remembers the movements \Nthey made within this segment of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.73,0:04:51.85,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,The clouds in the sky don't \Nrealize they've broken apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.11,0:04:56.94,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,A flame that's extinguished doesn't even \Nrealize the moment it went out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.33,0:04:59.90,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,All that remains in this \Nworld are the results.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.25,0:05:05.07,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,In the world where time has been eliminated, \Nall movement becomes pointless!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.47,0:05:09.22,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,I am the only one who can \Nreact to these movements.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.22,0:05:12.37,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,I can see every single \None of your movements!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.37,0:05:15.75,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,This is Emperor Crimson's ability!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.25,0:05:35.47,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Th-This ability...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.47,0:05:37.65,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,No matter who you may be,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.65,0:05:41.54,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,everyone goes through their ups and downs.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.54,0:05:44.27,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,You succeed, and you fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.75,0:05:51.30,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,But if you happen to find the pitfall known \Nas the future that's right in front of you
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.30,0:05:53.58,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,and manage to not fall in,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.58,0:05:56.50,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,you will never experience \Na setback in your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.38,0:06:00.88,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,You will remain in your best condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.25,0:06:02.96,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.45,0:06:15.47,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I've actually met you, \NI can tell that we are indeed related.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.09,0:06:21.11,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,I can sense that you are, \Nwithout a doubt, my daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.99,0:06:24.23,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.79,0:06:30.41,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,When you are awake, you will feel \Nthe exact same way toward me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.68,0:06:32.98,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Trish...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.98,0:06:36.83,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,I must fill any pitfall \Nthat threatens my path!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.12,0:06:40.66,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,I will now sever this bond \Nof blood that binds us!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.66,0:06:42.04,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Trish!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.79,0:06:44.17,sign_11970_145_Crunch,Sfx,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H5EFFF8&\4c&H519AEE&}Dogyuuuuun
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.17,0:06:44.92,sign_11970_145_Crunch,Sfx,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H5EFFF8&\4c&H519AEE&\clip(m 351 18 l 358 52 213 57 210 18)}Dogyuuuuun
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.45,0:06:48.72,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.77,0:06:54.82,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,That must be Giorno...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.67,0:06:59.06,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Giorno's Golden Wind's ability...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.55,0:07:03.73,JoJo-internal/narrator,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,He planted the turtle's cells in \Nthe brooch and gave it life,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.50,0:07:07.69,JoJo-internal/narrator,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,and a turtle with Stand abilities was born.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.98,0:07:11.12,JoJo-internal/narrator,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Since our call was interrupted, \Nhe must've sensed something was wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.12,0:07:12.66,JoJo-internal/narrator,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,and activated his ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.88,0:07:17.29,JoJo-internal/narrator,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,He always gives me courage...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.36,0:07:21.92,JoJo-internal/narrator,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think I could move \Nanymore, but... Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.27,0:07:24.28,JoJo-internal/narrator,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,I still...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.32,0:07:27.85,JoJo-internal/narrator,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,have to keep moving a little bit more.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.57,0:07:32.59,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,My mission's done? You're wrong, Boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.07,0:07:34.56,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,It's still ongoing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.14,0:07:36.39,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,As for Trish...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.80,0:07:39.60,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,I will protect her on my own order!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.84,0:07:43.51,JoJo-internal/narrator,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,If he can read all of my attacks,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.51,0:07:47.26,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,and I can't even realize \Nthat he's dodged them,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.79,0:07:52.16,JoJo-internal/narrator,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,then his ability surpasses \Nall others in its invincibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.13,0:07:56.57,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.87,0:08:03.54,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,This ability doesn't allow him to \Nread one's movements for long!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.23,0:08:06.04,JoJo-internal/narrator,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,It's only a short time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.39,0:08:09.35,JoJo-internal/narrator,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,It seems to be around five to ten seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.18,0:08:11.40,JoJo-internal/narrator,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Distance...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.40,0:08:13.80,JoJo-internal/narrator,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,For now, I need to get \Nas far away as possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.70,0:08:17.53,JoJo-internal/narrator,Burno,0000,0000,0000,,I need to get far enough that \Nthe boss can't find Trish!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.46,0:08:21.89,JoJo-internal/narrator,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,I beg of you to keep moving, body.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.70,0:08:25.26,JoJo-internal/narrator,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let me waste this \Nchance that Giorno gave me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.22,0:08:29.15,JoJo-internal/narrator,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Until I can get out of this basement...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.15,0:08:32.46,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,It seems there was another traitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.16,0:08:34.53,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,Must be the newbie.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.55,0:08:37.65,sign_11970_145_Crunch,Sfx,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H7B0BAF&\3c&H1A0744&\4c&H4002C7&}Rumble
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.03,0:08:39.77,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,If my information is correct, \NI believe his name is Giorno Giovanna.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.06,0:08:44.74,sign_11970_145_Crunch,Sfx,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H7B0BAF&\3c&H1A0744&\4c&H4002C7&}Rumble
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.39,0:08:44.75,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,So he must've joined this organization with \Nthe intent to betray me from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.42,0:08:48.97,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,It seems you thought you could escape \Njust by distancing yourself from me,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.97,0:08:52.46,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,but it's nothing for me to escape \Nthat turtle an instant sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.93,0:08:56.39,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,It appears that your efforts \Nwere futile, Bucciarati.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.46,0:08:59.64,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,How are you still able to move?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.64,0:09:01.06,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheer willpower?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.29,0:09:05.61,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,If you just rest, you won't be \Nable to get to the first floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.61,0:09:08.02,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,but you'll be able to die peacefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.84,0:09:11.65,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,First, I'm going to eliminate Trish.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.97,0:09:14.79,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you dare move, Bucciarati!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.79,0:09:18.09,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,The chance that Giorno gave me wasn't in vain!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.09,0:09:20.41,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,If this is going to be about \Nreading each other's moves,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.41,0:09:22.20,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,I've already read yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.93,0:09:25.25,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,I knew before you fell into the sewer
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.25,0:09:28.17,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,that you'd probably use \Nyour ability to escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.17,0:09:31.21,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Now, Zipper Man!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.40,0:09:33.91,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,Emperor Crimson!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.46,0:09:45.81,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,That was close...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.58,0:09:49.65,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,But within Emperor Crimson's world,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.24,0:09:53.23,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,your efforts are still futile!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.57,0:09:54.44,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,Take this!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.84,0:09:56.10,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,You're finished!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.90,0:09:59.24,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't you that I was trying to attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.24,0:10:00.91,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,It was this pillar!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.91,0:10:03.08,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Zipper, close!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.75,0:10:05.79,JoJo-main,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.79,0:10:09.72,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,As I thought... \NYour ability is invincible...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.72,0:10:14.23,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,But it appears that you can only \Nread movements for a short time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.23,0:10:17.38,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,You're not reading ahead of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.44,0:10:22.35,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Just try and read my future \Nmovements, Boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.80,0:10:26.41,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Try to figure out what I'm going \Nto do in a few seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.94,0:10:29.31,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Try to see beyond time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.74,0:10:32.02,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,You should be able to see me
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.64,0:10:34.21,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,after I've reached the first floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.81,0:10:47.66,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,Bucciarati! Trish!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.94,0:10:52.04,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,This wound...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.35,0:10:53.88,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,What happened in the basement?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.39,0:10:57.34,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,Where's the boss?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.19,0:11:01.42,JoJo-internal/narrator,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,He should still be around...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.87,0:11:03.64,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,Somewhere close by.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.51,0:11:08.06,JoJo-internal/narrator,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know the whole situation, \Nbut there's no way
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.06,0:11:11.33,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,the boss is just going to \Nlet Bucciarati go after this!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.46,0:11:20.52,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,Bucciarati...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.33,0:11:24.45,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,N-No...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.84,0:11:25.78,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,Bucciarati!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.24,0:11:34.38,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,His pulse...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.62,0:11:36.59,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,I-Impossible! It's gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.13,0:11:40.13,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,I created the parts needed for his recovery!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.13,0:11:42.16,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,Bucciarati, please breathe!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.82,0:11:44.98,JoJo-internal/narrator,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,So this must be Giorno Giovanna.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.73,0:11:51.64,JoJo-internal/narrator,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,His unknown ability gave Bucciarati \Nthe chance to escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.64,0:11:52.44,JoJo-internal/narrator,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.28,0:11:55.23,JoJo-internal/narrator,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,I will not let them get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.68,0:11:56.97,JoJo-main,gio,0000,0000,0000,,This is impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.41,0:11:58.94,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,I know I created the parts!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.60,0:12:01.62,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way he shouldn't have a heartbeat!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.62,0:12:03.41,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Giorno, it's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.21,0:12:05.78,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Call Abbacchio and the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.16,0:12:07.33,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.43,0:12:11.78,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,That voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.25,0:12:15.25,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,I told you to call Abbacchio and the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.84,0:12:17.09,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.58,0:12:18.92,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Out of this church!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.56,0:12:20.33,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.33,0:12:21.88,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,B-Bucciarati!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.14,0:12:23.26,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Thank goodness!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.68,0:12:24.67,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,You're okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.67,0:12:27.18,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry! Hurry up and call the others!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.18,0:12:28.85,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.85,0:12:32.34,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,We can't figure out who the \Nboss actually is right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.34,0:12:35.06,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,We need to get out of here, Giorno! \NWhile we're still far enough from him!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.06,0:12:36.82,JoJo-internal/narrator,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,They're within my range!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.82,0:12:37.65,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I go!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.94,0:12:42.66,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,I'll explain later! Hurry up, Giorno!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.76,0:12:45.83,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,Golden Wind!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.20,0:12:52.79,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,Giorno's over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.78,0:12:56.62,JoJo-main,Abba,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Giorno, you bastard! Come back here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.62,0:13:00.35,JoJo-main,Abba,0000,0000,0000,,How are you gonna make up for disobeying \Norders and stepping onto the island?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.35,0:13:01.84,JoJo-main,Mista,0000,0000,0000,,Bucciarati's here, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.03,0:13:04.36,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,H-How the hell did you get so injured?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.36,0:13:06.43,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you still have Trish with you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.70,0:13:08.88,JoJo-main,Abba,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on here, Bucciarati?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.88,0:13:10.16,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,I'll explain everything later.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.16,0:13:12.10,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, we need to get out \Nof here as fast as we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.39,0:13:14.59,JoJo-internal/narrator,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,I commend you, Bucciarati.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.30,0:13:18.72,JoJo-internal/narrator,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,I commend your precise and \Nkeen decision making.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.72,0:13:21.27,JoJo-internal/narrator,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,Even though I have the \Nability to eliminate time,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.76,0:13:24.90,JoJo-internal/narrator,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,if I were to face all six of those Stand users,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.90,0:13:27.16,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,one of them would end up \Nlearning my true identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.78,0:13:33.41,JoJo-internal/narrator,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,For the moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.82,0:13:37.00,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,they've managed to escape \Nmy Emperor Crimson.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.48,0:13:40.75,JoJo-internal/narrator,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,But this is not the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.21,0:13:42.38,JoJo-internal/narrator,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,I will never...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.76,0:13:44.63,JoJo-internal/narrator,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,let you escape
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.63,0:13:46.61,JoJo-internal/narrator,Boss,0000,0000,0000,,from Venice!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.55,0:13:53.97,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Now I understand why the boss is feared by \Neveryone and how he ruled over all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.40,0:13:56.82,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,We can't defeat the boss... not now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.67,0:13:59.24,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,As for his identity...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.24,0:14:01.57,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Assuming it even has one,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.14,0:14:05.23,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,we'll need to find his \Nability's weakness first!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.87,0:14:11.91,JoJo-Eyecatch2,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(145,1)}Emperor Crimson
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.26,0:14:14.30,JoJo-main,Mista,0000,0000,0000,,What...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.63,0:14:16.61,JoJo-main,Abba,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell's going on, Bucciarati?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.96,0:14:18.38,JoJo-main,Abba,0000,0000,0000,,We need an explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.38,0:14:20.26,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.29,0:14:24.78,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,All right. I'll just come out and say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.91,0:14:28.78,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,But I can't explain everything right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.78,0:14:31.89,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,because there's no time and \Ndanger's right around the corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.53,0:14:36.32,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,The reason I brought Trish back
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.86,0:14:38.94,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,is because I betrayed the boss just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.34,0:14:42.15,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be leaving you guys now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.73,0:14:48.15,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,If you go with me, \Nyou will also become traitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.50,0:14:50.23,JoJo-main,Mista,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.23,0:14:52.60,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,I-I don't think I heard you right...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.60,0:14:54.87,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What did you just say?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.87,0:14:58.62,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,He said... he betrayed the boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.93,0:15:00.33,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,B-But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.24,0:15:04.04,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,You probably shouldn't hear any more,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.72,0:15:07.28,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,because you guys have \Nnothing to do with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.19,0:15:10.20,JoJo-main,Giorno,0000,0000,0000,,I think you should explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.66,0:15:13.47,JoJo-main,Giorno,0000,0000,0000,,Some of them might want to follow you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.01,0:15:16.35,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,We need people on our side.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.40,0:15:21.10,JoJo-main,Abba,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is your deal, Giorno?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.10,0:15:24.19,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,First, you go into the church \Nwithout permission, and now—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.46,0:15:26.54,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,Bucciarati!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.15,0:15:29.28,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong? Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.28,0:15:30.68,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.31,0:15:34.68,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,I lost a lot of blood, so I got a bit dizzy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.35,0:15:37.00,JoJo-internal/narrator,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,That shouldn't be possible...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.33,0:15:40.23,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,When I created his parts, it should've \Nalso replenished the blood he lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.84,0:15:42.59,JoJo-internal/narrator,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,Did I miss a wound?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.92,0:15:48.40,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I've used up a good deal of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.40,0:15:52.41,JoJo-internal/narrator,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,Does he not feel pain? There was no \Nblood coming from the wound, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.79,0:15:53.80,JoJo-internal/narrator,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,Was I just seeing things?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.80,0:15:55.08,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.08,0:15:56.92,JoJo-main,Mista,0000,0000,0000,,You had me worried for a sec!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.92,0:15:58.30,JoJo-main,Abba,0000,0000,0000,,For real.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.30,0:16:00.23,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,Bucciarati, please...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.63,0:16:02.23,JoJo-main,Abba,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, Bucciarati.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.68,0:16:04.56,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,We want to know the details.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.81,0:16:15.57,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,The boss had us act as her bodyguards
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.57,0:16:20.17,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,so that he could kill his daughter \Nwith his own two hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.73,0:16:24.04,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Because she shares his blood, she could \Nhave figured out his true identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.61,0:16:26.71,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,I found that out and...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.50,0:16:29.49,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't forgive him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.49,0:16:33.48,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't just come back\Npretending I didn't see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.29,0:16:35.81,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I betrayed him!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.46,0:16:37.87,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,How could you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.87,0:16:40.22,JoJo-main,Mista,0000,0000,0000,,Are you insane, Bucciarati?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.65,0:16:43.58,JoJo-main,Abba,0000,0000,0000,,You know exactly what happens to traitors,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.58,0:16:45.66,JoJo-main,Abba,0000,0000,0000,,no matter who it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.66,0:16:48.87,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,The boss never lets anyone get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.87,0:16:53.45,JoJo-main,Abba,0000,0000,0000,,Hell, Venice could already be \Nsurrounded by the boss's elite guard!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.64,0:16:57.01,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,You're right, and that's why \NI'm going to need help.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.62,0:16:59.70,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,If any of you are willing to accompany me,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.40,0:17:02.98,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,come down these stairs and get on the boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.66,0:17:07.67,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,But I will not order any \Nof you to come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.37,0:17:10.71,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,I won't even ask you to come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.29,0:17:13.47,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,I did this all on my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.47,0:17:16.39,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,So you don't need to feel\Nobligated to come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.39,0:17:19.85,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,This may come off as arrogant, \Nbut I'm going to say it anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.40,0:17:22.81,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,I did this because I believe I'm right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.47,0:17:24.47,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,I have no regrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.94,0:17:29.73,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Despite the world we live in, I want to \Ncontinue on the path that I believe in.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.18,0:17:31.73,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,If we can just find his weakness...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.20,0:17:33.93,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Though we're only fleeing for now,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.93,0:17:35.95,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,I will defeat the boss, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.43,0:17:38.41,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,I will find his weakness, no matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.66,0:18:03.20,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,I understand your reasons, and what \Nyou did was right, Bucciarati.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.68,0:18:06.19,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm going to be blunt...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.96,0:18:10.28,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,I hate to say it, but no one's \Ngoing to get on that boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.02,0:18:13.72,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,How could you let your \Nemotions take over like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.28,0:18:17.66,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,I owe you my life, but going with you \Nnow would be a different matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.27,0:18:20.23,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,You've lost sight of reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.55,0:18:23.87,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,No one can survive in this world \Non expectations alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.36,0:18:27.02,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,We can't survive without the organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.52,0:18:29.33,JoJo-main,Abba,0000,0000,0000,,Fugo's absolutely right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.61,0:18:32.67,JoJo-main,Abba,0000,0000,0000,,What you did is basically suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.67,0:18:34.73,JoJo-main,Abba,0000,0000,0000,,No matter where in the \Nworld you might run to,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.73,0:18:37.30,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,you'll never find a safe haven again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.56,0:18:40.93,JoJo-main,Abba,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I pledged my loyalty \Nto the organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.54,0:18:44.26,JoJo-main,Abba,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like I pledged my loyalty to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.19,0:18:48.48,JoJo-main,Abba,0000,0000,0000,,That being said...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.59,0:18:54.78,JoJo-main,Abba,0000,0000,0000,,I never had a home or place I wanted to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.68,0:18:57.89,JoJo-main,Abba,0000,0000,0000,,The only time I'm ever at ease
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.64,0:19:01.95,JoJo-main,Abba,0000,0000,0000,,is when I'm with you, Bucciarati.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.32,0:19:05.37,JoJo-main,Giorno,0000,0000,0000,,Abbacchio...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.03,0:19:09.79,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You can't be serious, Abbacchio!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.00,0:19:12.63,JoJo-main,Mista,0000,0000,0000,,If we actually manage to defeat the boss...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.63,0:19:14.59,JoJo-main,Mista,0000,0000,0000,,Considering my skills,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.10,0:19:17.13,JoJo-main,Mista,0000,0000,0000,,I'd say I'm next in line to become a capo.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.05,0:19:20.64,JoJo-main,Mista,0000,0000,0000,,Bucciarati's smart.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.64,0:19:23.78,JoJo-main,Mista,0000,0000,0000,,He never goes into a fight that \Nhe has no chance of winning.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.78,0:19:26.60,JoJo-main,Mista,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna strike it rich for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.30,0:19:29.21,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,Mista! Not you, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.65,0:19:32.65,JoJo-main,Mista,0000,0000,0000,,What are you going to do, Fugo?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.12,0:19:36.00,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,You've all l-lost your minds!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.00,0:19:37.86,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to be completely isolated!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.86,0:19:39.97,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going to run to?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.97,0:19:43.20,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,No, you won't even make it \Nout of Venice alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.20,0:19:44.26,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,Narancia,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.69,0:19:46.37,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,what are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.80,0:19:50.22,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,I-I... d-don't know what to do...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.74,0:19:52.50,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me, Bucciarati...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.72,0:19:55.32,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.32,0:19:57.18,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think I should go?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.53,0:19:58.38,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Are you scared?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.59,0:20:01.58,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... I'm r-really scared...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.58,0:20:03.99,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,B-But just order me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.99,0:20:07.46,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,If you order me to go with you, \NI'll be more confident!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.46,0:20:10.52,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing scares me, as long \Nas you order me to do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.52,0:20:11.56,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.05,0:20:15.55,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,This is one thing I can't order you to do.\NYou need to decide for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.55,0:20:19.49,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,You need to choose your own path.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.68,0:20:24.70,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,B-But I don't know what to do! I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.70,0:20:26.70,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,But let me just give you this warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.46,0:20:29.10,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Don't come with me, Narancia.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.73,0:20:31.41,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,You're not cut out for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.54,0:20:36.71,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.06,0:20:38.86,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be killed, without a doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.86,0:20:42.97,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,There are some things in this world that \Nyou just can't do, even if you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.32,0:20:46.68,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,Our job has always been dirty.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.68,0:20:49.72,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,How is this any different?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.18,0:20:53.81,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Even then... I can't lie to myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.90,0:20:57.95,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.95,0:21:01.53,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Once the boat takes off, \Nyou're officially traitors!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.86,0:21:08.58,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,Why? You're insane!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.58,0:21:13.05,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,All this for a woman you just \Nmet and barely talked to!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.05,0:21:16.04,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,You don't even know what \Nkind of music she likes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.74,0:21:25.05,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,Trish was abandoned by \Nthe people she trusted...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.30,0:21:30.38,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,I was also abandoned before.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.94,0:21:35.89,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,I was abandoned by my dad \Nand the friends I trusted.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.56,0:21:40.36,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,We're sort of alike...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.14,0:21:40.36,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}It's none of our business what \Nthe boss does with his daughter!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.81,0:21:44.69,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,Trish and I are sort of alike!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.81,0:21:44.69,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}All he had to do was close his eyes! \NI just don't understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.43,0:21:49.54,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Giorno, give me the turtle.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.43,0:21:52.26,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Let's put Trish inside it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.26,0:21:53.10,JoJo-main,Giorno,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.92,0:21:57.49,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,Bucciarati, please turn around.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.49,0:22:01.42,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,Bucciarati!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.11,0:22:06.01,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go! I'll go, too! I'm coming with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.47,0:22:09.44,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,Don't order me not to go with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.44,0:22:15.32,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,Trish is me! She's me! \NThe wound on her arm is my own!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.64,0:22:21.12,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,Narancia... Not you, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.85,0:22:24.69,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,You fool... You're going to be killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.56,0:22:32.02,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,I can't go along with \Nsuch a foolish betrayal.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.68,0:22:35.34,JoJo-main,Fugo,0000,0000,0000,,I can't become a righteous idiot...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.26,0:22:43.98,JoJo-main,Mista,0000,0000,0000,,You took way too long to make your decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.98,0:22:47.01,JoJo-main,Abba,0000,0000,0000,,You'd better not hold this\Nagainst us later on.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.33,0:22:50.64,JoJo-main,Gio,0000,0000,0000,,Narancia, I have nothing but \Nrespect for your courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.71,0:22:54.27,JoJo-main,Mista,0000,0000,0000,,I guess Fugo didn't come after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.62,0:22:57.64,JoJo-main,Abba,0000,0000,0000,,That was his choice to make.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.61,0:23:02.56,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,Bucciarati!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.89,0:23:05.66,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,I... I want to protect Trish!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.25,0:23:08.03,JoJo-main,Nara,0000,0000,0000,,I'll defeat the boss with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.88,0:23:09.83,JoJo-main,Bruno,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.58,0:23:20.07,JoJo-main,Doppio,0000,0000,0000,,Squalo?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.07,0:23:23.98,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,We have some traitors... in Venice.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.98,0:23:28.88,JoJo-main,Doppio,0000,0000,0000,,The names of the traitors are \NBruno Bucciarati and Giorno Giovanna.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.01,0:23:33.05,sign_33760_385_The_boss_s_ident,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(64,40)\fad(438,598)}The boss's identity: Unknown\NStand name: Emperor Crimson\N\NHas the ability to eliminate a certain amount of time.\NBecause of this, he can predict the future. Invincible.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.88,0:23:31.54,JoJo-main,Doppio,0000,0000,0000,,They can be taken dead or alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.54,0:23:33.29,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,This is straight from the boss!
